1 Pre-processing

1.1 Importing Dataset

data <- read_sav('MVDA_Assignment3_FA&LRA_ProductReturns_1.sav')

1.2 Data Formatting

data$CustomerID <- as.factor(data$CustomerID)
data$ProductCategory <- as.factor(data$ProductCategory)
data$Style <- as.factor(data$Style)
data$Gender <- factor(data$Gender, levels = c(1,2), labels = c("Male", "Female"))
data$ItemReturn <- factor(data$ItemReturn, levels = c(0,1), labels = c("Not Returned", "Returned"))
data$ItemDiscount <- factor(data$ItemDiscount, levels = c(0,1), labels = c("Not Discounted", "Discounted"))

3.6 Leaving One Out Cross Validation

acc <- NULL

for(i in 1:nrow(data))
{
    # Train-test splitting
    train <- data[-i,]
    test <- data[i,]
    
    # Fitting
    model <- glm(ItemReturn ~ Gender + OrderValue + ItemPrice + RetailerLoyalty + PreferOnline + PriceSensitivity,
                 data=train, family=binomial)
    
    # Predict results
    results_prob <- predict(model, type='response')
    
    # If prob > 0.5 then 1, else 0
    results <- ifelse(results_prob > 0.5, 1, 0)
    
    # Actual answers
    answers <- test$ItemReturn
    
    # Calculate accuracy
    misClasificError <- mean(answers != results)
    
    # Collecting results
    acc[i] <- 1-misClasificError
}

# Average accuracy of the model
mean(acc)
## [1] 0.8644603
